post_text: THANK YOU to the faculty and staff members who literally risked their own health to distribute food to our kids today. We prepared for 430 children based on the parental contacts made last week. We served 532 children. Each child received 6 meals for a total of 3,192 meals served! Unfortunately, we ran out of food before we could serve all those in line. We’ll learn from today and hopefully be better prepared on Thursday!

post_text: The Alabama State Department of Education released the annual report card for schools and districts earlier today. We are pleased to announce that our district earned a 93/A, which is an improvement of one point over last year’s score. This scores places us among the 26 districts in the state that earned an A. Our score is also the 6th highest score earned by any district in the state. We are also proud of the scores earned by our individual schools: MSHS- 90/A, MSMS- 93/A, and MCBride Elementary- 89/B. Our students and teachers worked hard to earn these marks. We are honored to serve a community with high expectations for academic excellence!

post_text: The purpose of the following video is to clear up misinformation that has been distributed on social media in an attempt to create distrust and defeat the initiative to approve the 5 mill tax referendum.
text: The purpose of the following video is to clear up misinformation that has been distributed on social media in an attempt to create distrust and defeat the initiative to approve the 5 mill tax referendum.

post_text: Actual Tax Cost - The 5 mills tax referendum is NOT a 67% Increase in Home Taxes as some have mentioned. It is actually a 67% increase on mills, not on taxes paid. The simple math is the taxpayer cost will be $50 a year for every $100,000 of assessed value of your home. For example a home that is appraised at $200,000 will have a tax increase of $100 a year or $8.33 a month. We want every citizen to have factual information to make an informed decision.
text: Actual Tax Cost - The 5 mills tax referendum is NOT a 67% Increase in Home Taxes as some have mentioned. It is actually a 67% increase on mills, not on taxes paid. The simple math is the taxpayer cost will be $50 a year for every $100,000 of assessed value of your home. For example a home that is appraised at $200,000 will have a tax increase of $100 a year or $8.33 a month. We want every citizen to have factual information to make an informed decision.

Please note the following:
-The “yellow” team bus on the 8th grade field trip was sideswiped this morning in Philadelphia.
-ALL STUDENTS and PARENTS are FINE. There were no injuries.
-The students are already at the first touring destination of the day.

We are thankful for their safety!

post_text:
Be sure and vote on the tax renewal on Tuesday, April 28, 2015. This tax provides Muscle Shoals City Schools with an average of 1.2 million dollars per year. The money is used for yearly operating expenses such as local teacher units, utilities, transportation, custodial supplies, and unanticipated capital expenditures. Your vote is important! Please vote on the tax renewal next Tuesday. Thank you for supporting the children of Muscle Shoals City Schools.
Go Trojans!
